      • RestResponse

        public RestResponse(int _statusCode,
                    java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> _headers,
                    java.lang.String _body)
        Will create a RestResponse and load the response data to it.
        Parameters:
        _statusCode - The Response Code that was returned.
        _headers - The Response Header Key/Value pairs that were returned.
        _body - The Body of the Response message.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the Response Code is invalid (<100 or >599).

        If the given Response Headers is null or empty.

        If the given Response Body is null. (If the Response Body is empty, use an empty String.)
